cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on the task of identifying semantic relations between words. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques and the use of distributional feature representations, which suggests that it could also fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the task of query expansion in information retrieval (IR), which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of semi-supervised learning, which could also place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
